cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation of robotic instruments in surgical scenes using deep learning-based approaches. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with the problem of tracking and pose estimation of instruments, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep neural networks for instrument segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of multi-class segmentation, which may fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of deep learning-based approaches for instrument segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
